Please inquire with the shelter.<p/> Current Location: In RASKC Foster Home <p/>Karl is a big guy with a matching cattitude. He would be best as the only pet in the house unless he could get a proper (and long) introduction, as he thinks he is the alpha male. In foster care he tolerates three other cats that are all submissive. He was traumatized by the death of his owner when he was brought in to RASKC, and after two months in foster care he has settled down quite a bit. Sometimes he will jump up on your lap, headbutt you and purr, and a few minutes later hiss and jump down. At this time he needs a forever home with lots of attention so he can settle into being a happy cat all of the time. Note that it has taken several weeks to get to where he is now and will likely regress some when he moves. It will require some patience but it will be well worth it as he can be a big, loving and cuddly kitty. He'll even sleep under the covers with you.<p/><p/>Karl is not a picky eater and is 100% when it comes to the litter box. He marks his "territory" with a headbutt only and does not spray (whew!). He loves his cardboard scratching post and is absolutely crazy about catnip and his catnip banana. A laser pointer is a must as is a feather on a string for play. He is an exclusively inside cat but does like to spend some time in the catio to get away.<p/><p/>You can meet Karl at his foster home and have any of your questions answered.<p/>
